        "text": "The document is a \"Market Participation Demand Response Registration Checklist\" for registering demand response resources in an ISO market. It includes a flowchart and a checklist:\n\n**Flowchart Steps:**\n1. DRP (Demand Response Provider) creates location(s).\n2. Location(s) approved by LSE (Load Serving Entity) and UDC (Utility Distribution Company).\n3. DRP registers location(s).\n4. Registration confirmed in DRRS (Demand Response Registration System).\n5. DRP submits GRDT (Generator Resource Data Template) form for Master File.\n6. PDR/RDRR (Proxy Demand Resource/Real-Time Demand Response Resource) IDs and characteristics added to ISO Master File.\n7. Resource becomes active in ISO Market.\n\n**Checklist Items:**\n- **Information Request Sheet:** Submitted.\n- **Demand Response Provider Agreement (DRPA):** Received for review and executed (signed/returned).\n- **Demand Response Provider ID:** Assigned by ISO.\n- **Scheduling Coordinator Assignment:** Obtained.\n- **Demand Response System Access (DRRS):** AIM request submitted, certificate received, and access verified for production and map stage environments.\n\nEach checklist item has a corresponding checkbox for tracking completion.",
